    {
      "title": "Review of Verb Conjugation",
      "titleArabic": "مراجعة تصريف الأفعال",
      "content": [
        "Past tense verbs change endings based on the subject: كَتَبَ، كَتَبَتْ، كَتَبْتُ، كَتَبْنَا.",
        "Present tense verbs use prefixes and suffixes: يَكْتُبُ، تَكْتُبُ، أَكْتُبُ، نَكْتُبُ."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Past: ذَهَبَ (he went), ذَهَبَتْ (she went), ذَهَبْتُ (I went)",
